$interpreted: Theodore: You plan on assassinating Angelia?
Karen: Yes. During the coronation ceremony, I plan to let the counterfeit gemstone explode and take her out in exchange for my own life.
Theodore: Who told you to take these unnecessary actions!
Karen: If we miss this opportunity, Angelia will be formally appointed as Queen. If I can sacrifice myself to remove her,
Karen: Your Majesty Theodore will be able to...
Theodore: Shut your mouth! You really think this is going to work?
Theodore: I've already thought about what ought to be done. I don't need you making decisions for me!
Theodore: That's all. Go back to where you came from.
Karen: Then what should I do now? Please, Your Majesty Theodore, give me an order. I will definitely try my best to...
Theodore: What you should do, what identity to take on, those are your own decisions to make! Don't bother me with these insignificant matters!
Karen: His Majesty wants me to make my own decisions...ten years ago, His Majesty visited the blood-ridden war zone on King William's orders.
Karen: That day, His Majesty recused me from that hell. Since then, I've only ever acted on his orders...
Bodyguard: Didn't His Majesty say to not do anything unnecessary anymore? What will you do if you expose His Majesty's whereabouts?
Karen: For over ten years, I've only ever followed His Majesty's commands whenever I did anything. If I had to make my own choice...
Bodyguard: Hey! Where are you going? Before we're certain that you won't be a burden to His Majesty, you're not approved to go anywhere!
Karen: I don't think His Majesty is suited for such a desolate desert.
Karen: Please inform His Majesty that, for the time being, I'll be taking a temporary leave from the Desert Bazaar.
